ca-name: The name of the extension (normally WSArrays)
ca-description: The description of the extension as shown on Special:Version
ca-omitted: Error message shown when someone forgets a required parameter
ca-map-multidimensional: Error message shown when someone tries to map a multidimensional array using #complexarrayprint
ca-nonexistent-subarray: Error message shown when someone tries to push a value to a non-existent subarray
ca-undefined-array: Error message shown when someone tries to apply transactions or print a non-existent array
ca-subarray-not-provided: Error message shown when someone omits a subarray
ca-invalid-name: Error message shown when someone tries to apply transactions to an invalid name
ca-invalid-wson: Error message shown when someone uses invalid WSON
ca-max-defined-arrays-reached: Error message shown when someone tries to define too many arrays
ca-sort-missing-key: Error message shown when someone omits the key while using keysort
ca-sort-array-too-deep: Error message shown when someone tries to use keysort on an array that isn't two-dimensional
ca-sort-broken: Error message shown when the sorting failed
ca-too-little-arrays: Error message shown when less than two arrays are given to the parser function #complexarraymerge or #complexarraypusharray
ca-nonexistent-multiple: Error message shown when one or more of the arrays given does not exist
ca-unsupported-version: Exception thrown when some version is not supported
ca-smw-paramdesc-name: Description of the SMW printer parameter 'name'
ca-smw-paramdesc-hide: Description of the SMW printer parameter 'hide'
ca-smw-paramdesc-unassociative: Description of the SMW printer parameter 'unassociative'
ca-smw-paramdesc-detailed: Description of the SMW printer parameter 'simple'
ca-smw-paramdesc-valuesep: Description of the SMW printer parameter 'valuesep'
ca-invalid-markup: Error message shown when the markup used is not recognized
ca-sort-invalid-key: Error message shown when an invalid sort key is used
